The paper discusses algorithms and data structures used for dynamic graphs, which are commonly used in computer science applications such as graphics, communication networks, and VLSI designs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.GR (Graphics). Among these, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the topic of dynamic graph algorithms and data structures. The other categories are also possible as they involve applications of dynamic graphs in various fields.
